Wash and dry all produce. Core and seed @poblano pepper{1}, then thinly slice crosswise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Finely dice a few slices until you have 3 TBSP diced onion and set aside for garnish. Drain @pineapple{1}. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Pick @cilantro{1/4%cup} leaves from stems; discard stems.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and sliced onion. Cook, tossing, until lightly charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add pineapple to pan and cook, tossing, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chipotle seitan crumbles{8} to pan. Cook, tossing, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @southwest spice blend{} and @chipotle powder{} (to taste—start with a pinch and go up from there). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortilla{6} in a damp #paper towel{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

> Alternatively, wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven for 5 minutes at 400 degrees.

Spread a bit of @sour cream{4%tbsp} on each tortilla, then top with seitan, veggies, diced onion, and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.